arch:property.oc:show_val: Major collapse and architectural overburden throughout the Theater area.
Closing Levels: 886.54 masl at NW, 886.56 masl at C, 886.30 masl at SW, 886.69 masl at east.
Opening Levels: 906.816 masl at northwest, 907.656 masl at northeast, 907.016 masl at center, 896.886 masl at southwest, 907.506 masl at southeast.

7.5 YR 4/4 (brown). Dense rubble layer, representing collapse of the intercolumnar and east exterior walls, and other features. It was highest on the east, and then sloped down westward into the "bowl" of the theatron. Full of architectural fragments (and stucco fragments in the East Corridor), this layer was nonetheless relatively free of other kinds of artifactual materials.
Phase XI: Further collapse post CE 5th c., possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512. The east Porch columns and Central Arch collapse and fluvial deposits continue to accumulate.
